<P>The contents of the writing was, <HI>O faithle&s;s man! What more need I exhibit unto you! I am the &s;pirit of a ju&s;t man&punc; &s;ent from Heaven to declare the&s;e things unto you; and I can have no re&s;t until I have delivered great po&s;&s;e&s;&s;ions into your hands; but look to</HI> GOD, <HI>there is greater trea&s;ure in Heaven for you! O faithle&s;s men! Pre&s;s forward in faith, and the prize is yours!</HI> It <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> mentioned various chapters in the Bible, that the members mu&s;t peru&s;e, and particular p&s;alms for them to &s;ing; and the company mu&s;t con&s;i&s;t of thirty &s;even members; and each man mu&s;t depo&s;it into the hands of the &s;pirit according to his circum&s;tances, not ex|ceeding twelve, nor le&s;s than &s;ix pounds; and the mo|ney mu&s;t be given up as &s;oon as po&s;&s;ible, in order to relieve the &s;pirit from his exigencies, that he might return from whence he came.</P>
